		<p>I don&#8217;t buy the whole &#8220;if Netflix didn&#8217;t have DRM, there wouldn&#8217;t be any streaming&#8221; argument. If you really want to steal a movie, odds are you can find 9 out of 10 movies on Netflix on a torrent site within minutes.<br />
What Netflix offer is convenience. That&#8217;s what keeping streaming services in business, not DRM. DRM has never stopped piracy, and it never will. That whole argument is flawed.<br />
And, I might add, it&#8217;s usually easier to find a torrent for a movie and download that, than it is to save/extract a stream to your harddrive.</p>
